events.name: DevFest 2018 Ikorodu
events.description:
DevFest is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas and interests! We are excited to bring the DevFest18 energy to Ikorodu this year! We would be showcasing multiple speaker sessions in multiple google products area such as:
Google Cloud
Web
Mobile
Internet of Things (IoT)
Open-source etc
events.how_to_find_us: 58B Lagos road behind Access Bank, Opposite UBA, Benson bus-stop, Ikorodu, Lagos

events.name: Cloud Study Jam
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us at GDG Ikorodu for our Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training that is worth more than $55 in value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.
Then after our Cloud Study Jam live session, you will have free access to more labs that you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to complete any labs you want.

Requirements?
What we only require from you is to bring your laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers.

For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.
Once again...... Don’t forget your charger.

Cheers!!!
events.how_to_find_us: From Benson bus-stop, Ikorodu, cross to the other side of the road. Pass beside the Access bank. The event center is just behind Access bank.

events.name: Google I/O Extended 2019
events.description:
Google I/O is a developer festival that is going to be held by May 7 - 9 at the Shoreline Amphitheatre in Mountain View, California.

I/O brings together developers from around the globe annually for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and a first look at Google’s latest developer products.

Come be a part of the I/O energy, cool product release and excitement at our local extended party at GDG Ikorodu.

upcoming.name: IWD IKORODU 2020
upcoming.description:
Women Techmakers (WTM) Ikorodu

Among the amazing opportunities that comes with the WTM communities is the International Womens Day(IWD) Celebrations.

Celebrating the women in STEM and beyond, WTM Communities from all over the world are continuously holding incredible events to provide an opportunity for their communities to have an experience of the IWD Summits that are held in various countries all over the world.

Join Women Techmakers Ikorodu on 18th of april 2020 as they hold an amazing maiden event.

Tell a friend and come for inspirational talks, hands on codelabs, icebreakers, access to amazing communication building workshops and a customized networking experience.

We can't wait to see you there!

What to bring:
-Your Laptop and internet
-A notebook and a Pen
-Excitement
-A friend!!!

To get more highlights, kindly follow our official twitter page

https://mobile.twitter.com/WTMIkorodu

Note:
The event is welcome to all.
